#Artificial Intelligence vs. Augmented Intelligence

⚫Types of Intelligence

1. Human Intelligence
Natural ability of humans to think, decide, learn, and feel emotions.

2. Artificial Intelligence (AI)
Machines perform tasks that normally require human intelligence.
➜ Works independently, minimal or no human involvement.

3. Augmented Intelligence (AuI)
Humans and machines work together.
➜ AI supports and enhances human decision-making.

⚫Artificial Intelligence (AI)

Definition:
AI is the ability of machines to imitate human intelligence such as learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.

Key Characteristics:
◾Replaces human effort in specific tasks
◾Works automatically
◾High speed and accuracy

Strengths:
◾Handles huge amounts of data
◾Performs repetitive tasks efficiently
◾Works continuously without fatigue
◾Consistent and reliable

Examples:
◾Self-driving cars (full automation)
◾Data analysis systems
◾Chatbots and recommendation systems

⚫Augmented Intelligence (AuI)

Definition:
Augmented intelligence enhances human abilities using AI rather than replacing humans.

Key Characteristics:
◾Human-in-the-loop
◾Supports better decision-making
◾Focuses on collaboration

Strengths:
◾Combines machine speed with human judgment
◾Improves safety and productivity
◾Reduces human error

Examples:
◾Collision detection in cars
◾Blind-spot alerts
◾Screen readers for visually impaired
◾Voice-based navigation systems

⚫Humans vs. Machines (Strength Matrix)

Machines are good at:
◾Fast data processing
◾Repetitive and rule-based tasks
◾Accuracy and consistency

Humans are good at:
◾Creativity and innovation
◾Understanding context
◾Emotional intelligence
◾Communication and empathy

⚫Final Conclusion:
◾AI is best for automation and efficiency
◾Humans are best for creativity and emotional understanding
◾Augmented Intelligence is the ideal approach
◾Future success depends on humans and AI working together

| Artificial Intelligence | Augmented Intelligence |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Replaces humans         | Assists humans         |
| Fully automated         | Human + machine        |
| Task-focused            | Decision-focused       |

